title: Distributions and Plasma Moments, Definitive, Geotail CPI/SWA (Comprehensive Plasma Instrument / Solar Wind Analyzer) - L. Frank, W. Patterson and K. Ackerson (U. Iowa)

info.x_cadence_note: Counts based on variable 'Epoch' in https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/sp_phys/data/geotail/cpi/cpi_swa/1992/ge_sw_cpi_19921006_v01.cdf. The most common cadence, 48312 [ms] = PT48.312S, occurred for 48.7044% of the 827 timesteps.
info.contact: L. Frank, W. Patterson and K. Ackerson @ U. Iowa

parameters.name: Velocity
parameters.description: Ion Bulk Flow Spee(H only when in solar wind)

parameters.name: PolarAngle

parameters.name: Azimuthal
